cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IT

This paper deals with the global loss landscape of one-hidden-layer ReLU neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the activation pattern of hidden neurons, which is related to neural network architecture, and the probability of getting stuck in local minima, which is related to optimization. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for image classification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision), and the computation of probability, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
